					On the title <foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">mahānavakammika</foreign>, also occurring in EIAD 391<!-- link to be added-->, l. 1, see <bibl><ptr target="bib:Silk"/>: <citedRange>94</citedRange></bibl>; Kieffer-Pülz 2010: 78<!-- link to be added-->. The latter suggests that <quote>Possibly the term <foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">mahānavakamaka</foreign> ... is used in the sense ‘head <foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">navakamaka</foreign>’, and developed as a consequence of this specialization to distinguish him from <foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">navakarmika</foreign>s who were only responsible for parts of larger constructions (??).</quote><!-- Von Hinüber’s editions add a 20th line
